verbose_text: In the current study, analysis of TCGA generated colorectal adenocarcinoma data (TCGA, provisional) showed that patients whose colorectal tumors expressed high levels of TM4SF5 (Z> 1.5) had a significantly worse overall survival than those patients with lower levels of TM4SF5 (Z < = 1.5) in their tumors (n = 382, P = 0.0391).
